<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-318-886  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 318 886.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 5 1989 v6 n22 p16(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New hand-held scanner packs desktop power. (Mitsubishi ElectronicsAmerica Inc.'s Scan Kit) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bernard, Diane.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mitsubishi Electronics America Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Mitsubishi Electronics America Scan Kit (Scanning device) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Image processingScanningProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Diane BernardandM;Mitsubishi Electronics America Inc. recently unveiled a new scanner thatcombines the flexibility of a hand-held scanner with the functionality ofdesktop models, company officials said.andM;Mitsubishi's Scan Kit, available now for $995, features a detachablehand-held scanner attached to a sheet feeder, allowing users to eitherhand-scan full-sized documents or operate the unit as a desktop scanner byfeeding pages continuously, the officials said.andM;The scanner scans images at 10 seconds per page with a resolution of 200 dotsper inch, the officials said.andP;  It recognizes as many as 16 shades of gray andhas a scanning width of 8-1/2 inches, they added.andM;For users of WordPerfect 5.0, the Scan Kit installation guide includesspecial applications notes that explain how users can easily integrate thescanner software and WordPerfect, according to Dave Thompson, a spokesman forthe firm.andM;Scan Kit includes scanner utility software, an IBM PC-compatible controllerand the installation guide.andM;Mitsubishi, of Torrance, Calif., can be reached at (213) 515-3993.andO;</TEXT></DOC>